Another example, commonly used in [operations research](/Operations_research) courses, is the distribution of lifeguards on beaches (a.k.a. the "Life's a Beach" example). &#91;7&#93; The example describes two beaches with lifeguards to be distributed on each beach. There is maximum budget B that can be distributed among the two beaches (in total), and using a marginal returns table, analysts can decide how many lifeguards to allocate to each beach.  

